External Knowledge:
- "regular season" and "playoffs" refer to different stages of a sports league's schedule; 
- "average points per game" is a common metric to evaluate a player's performance, calculated by dividing the total points scored by the number of games played; 
- "difference in average points per game" and "changes from one season to the next" provide insights into a player's consistency and improvement or decline over time.
